      <div class="msgContentFrame">Buying gold for money is not permitted in wow. It is not. You get banned. Cops will not arrest you for it but you will get banned. <br /> <br />I think you can sell trade card game items in wow for gold. It's not actual RMT but TCG items come from real money, but that's about as far as you can go without earning yourself a ban. <br /> <br />Tradeskill materials have insane inflation and you collect them while leveling. You collect more if you have gathering skills like mining, herbalism and skinning. Fishing works too. <br /> <br />It depends on your server, on one server I play I've sold many stacks of Oily Blackmouth for 30g a piece, on another server the AH is full of Oily Blackmouth and the going price is 20 silvers a piece, you'll have to look at the supply in the AH. The materials in short supply are the ones you can gather and overprice madly. <br /> <br />The other part is learning how to spend your gold efficiently so that you don't drain your gold. For example, instead of spending hundreds on mage portals you can just buy one portal to dalaran and set hearthstone there, from then you can use the Dalaran portals to go wherever you want. <br /> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Jul  3rd 2010  5:39pm by xorq </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>NOTE: I may post comments about my like/dislike/approval/disapproval of game features. <br />1- They are NOT a complaint. They are a perspective. <br />2- They are NOT advocacy. They are a perspective. <br /> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Overlord Theophany wrote:</div><div class="orig">Insults aren't needed</div></div></div></div>
