      <div class="msgContentFrame">Another thing to pay attention to is your character's level; as your character goes up, making gold gets easier.  Don't get bogged down trying to make hundreds of gold at level 10.  Set goals according to what you'll need -- training, mounts and possibly dual spec.   <br /> <br />Spend wisely, read the quest rewards in the information about zones and look at drops in low level instances.  There is no point in buying stuff off the auction house that is no better than something you could get for free.  For that matter, low levels fly by now and you can probably push through a good number of them in less than optimal gear.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Wrong tone?  What, do you mean I just asked for donkey tea and a large bowl of sugar instead of green tea and soup?  /groan </div></div>
